## Inputs to Study Before Planning

Read ALL of the following before writing the plan:

1. **The current engagement area file** — `org-8.0/what-we-sell/strategy/engagement-areas/[ENGAGEMENT AREA FILENAME].md` — to understand what exists today and what needs to be replaced.
2. **The distillation framework** — `org-8.0/what-we-sell/strategy/distillation/how-to.md` — the Right to Play / Right to Win lens that the analysis must ultimately serve.
3. **The thesis** — `org-8.0/what-we-sell/the-thesis/thesis.md` — the structural argument that frames all of Zeta's strategy. The opportunity analysis must be compatible with (but independent of) this thesis.
4. **Related product-line files** — search `org-8.0/what-we-sell/strategy/product-lines/` for product families relevant to this engagement area. These define the Zeta assets that Part II will reference.
5. **The product-line-engineering archetype** (if one exists) — search `org-8.0/product-line-engineering/archetypes/` for this engagement area.
6. **The S.TODO** — `org-8.0/what-we-sell/strategy/S.TODO` — the user's original directive on tone and approach.
7. **The editorial rigor review skill** — `.cursor/skills/editorial-rigor-review/SKILL.md` — the eight editorial tests that Part I must pass. (Part II follows different rules — it is permitted to be commercial and prescriptive.)
8. **Existing research material** — check `org-8.0/what-we-sell/strategy/_research/` and `market-study/` for any previously conducted research that overlaps with this engagement area. Cross-reference rather than re-research.
9. **Other completed opportunity analyses** (if any exist beyond the capability-catalogue versions) — to calibrate depth and style.

